methods.applyTransform:
Calls a .update() on the underlying table with the given formula: underlyingTable.update(columnName = update)

:param columnName: (java.lang.String) - the resulting column
:param update: (java.lang.String) - the formula inside
:param classesToImport: (java.lang.Class[]) - classes to import into the query scope
:param params: (java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>) - parameters to add to the query scope
:param columnTypesPreserved: (boolean) - set to true if the update clause is 'add only' with respect to columns. This allows
        the copying of ACLs
